(10, 'Church', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcRG7uSaTUMrA6obW0I3DSLkWI-IuQBoyF86CpJRC1uUNTV0E8Bw&usqp=CAU', 'Hai Chau and Thanh Pho da Nang', 'The church is located on Ong Ich Khiem Street, Da Nang, built in 1931, is one of the largest Protestant churches in Da Nang city and also the first autonomous church of Viet Evangelical Church. South, even in Indochina was born.\r\n\r\nProtestant church in Da Nang, designed and built by American pastors RAFabbray, Paul M. Hoaster, G. Roy Huglers in 1913, made of wood and covered with leaves This was only 20 people belonging to the royal family Cong Ton Nu Thi Hau and Cong Ton Nu Tu Oanh (grandson of King Minh Mang). In 1920, the Church began to open a Bible class here. After the flood devastated the city, it was not until 1922 that the church was rebuilt with solid materials and until 2000, it was restored in modern architectural style.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCurrently, the church consists of a ground floor and a floor, the front wall is built high and above is a cross symbolizing the religion. Modern church architecture, simple. Inside, there are rows of chairs for worshipers like Christian churches, no images and in the sanctuary there is a cross symbolizing Jesus in need.', 'https://images.foody.vn/res/g24/231262/prof/s576x330/foody-mobile-t1-jpg-636-636095510365544508.jpg@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcSGrF3becGgJgcD5y-_So7Y9r68d53qVLL0jw&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcR4nsZ-uus9ax2czJOnDa_avmYiXT3lgj6dDw&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcTILefdkEiG0JsjRg9RsZ8cdN7s7gvEYHw6_w&usqp=CAU', 2, '16.071075', '108.213086'),
(11, 'Rựu Sim Sơn', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcR9tH8kf7ZRepC8tJLGOYTmuL5aBdMnJD3BnExH4Sbmi0WkyXZs&usqp=CAU', 'Duong silk, phu quoc, province abstain from extortion 922200', 'If you want to enjoy a certain kind of wine of Phu Quoc with strange, unique, delicious taste but also good for health, Sim Son wine is a great choice.\r\n\r\nSim Son wine brand is a famous wine brand in Phu Quoc with manual wine making method combined with new technological processing process, plus careful selection of raw materials and careful tempering process. meticulously produces a scrumptious, captivating wine for those who enjoy this Phu Quoc specialty.\r\n\r\nThe taste of it has a bit of intoxicating yeast and the sweet taste of the forest sims will satisfy the most fastidious diners.\r\nIndeed, among foreign wines, nowadays fake wine, Sim Son wine still stands and increasingly affirms its brand, proves that it is a good quality product, and is trusted by many people. We are very pleased and proud to be the one who brings you the Sim Son bottles of pure wine with great taste.', 'https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-kpUl1jEZ3j4/Vh9mhBxOL4I/AAAAAAAAA8s/jpflcpA3ZRQ0pMdtApLz1BHc8Csh7p7AwCPcBGAYYCw/s1600/ruou-sim-30.jpg@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQPT5mwrnXzaS8pBT-ZZwp3QgGbbpXOw-XdoQ&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcRJc5PklgHs_1FwgDCsYMLgUzuhndnQDCXsYQ&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcSiCSI_yYKT1bxw-4Fx8TmEYJUwMc91t0o_wg&usqp=CAU', 21, '16.068695', '108.223297'),
(12, 'Than Tai Hot Spring Park', 'https://cdn.yeudulich.com/940x630/media/attraction/attraction/VNMDAD16.jpg', 'QL14G, Hoà Phú, Hòa Vang, Đà Nẵng', 'Escape the city noise with this tour of the Godfather\'s Hot Springs Park!\r\nLocated deep in the mountains of Ba Na - Nui Chua Nature Reserve, this park offers a comfortable bathing experience\r\nSwim in the Jacuzzi and Lazy river at Long Tien Cave, impressive attractions you cannot miss!\r\nExperience the park\'s official onsen bath, the first onsen in Vietnam to meet Japanese standards\r\nTry a variety of special baths made up of hot minerals, mud, herbs, tea, milk and even wine!\r\nIf you have yet to find yourself in Danang, don\'t hesitate to take a bath at the newest hot spring location here - Shen Tai Hot Spring Park. Book a relaxing day trip through Klook at the town\'s waterfront talks. Surrounded by the greenery of Ba Na-Nui Chua Nature Reserve, Than Tai Hot Spring Park has many bathrooms; from mud baths and onsen baths to coffee, milk, tea and even alcohol baths. Experience one of these baths after your trip to the Temple of Fortune or continue to the Jacuzzi and Lazy River in Long Tien Cave. These warm swimming pools will ease muscular aches and pains, perfect for active locals and weary travelers. After a relaxing dip, enjoy a Vietnamese lunch at the restaurant and learn more about the park through an English speaking guide. Finish the tour by returning to your hotel in the center of Danang CityPlease note this schedule is for reference only and subject to traffic conditions of the day\r\n7:15 am-8: 15 am pick up at hotel in central Danang or meeting place\r\n8:45 am arrive at Than Tai Hot Spring Park\r\nVisit the Temple of Fortune\r\nEnjoy underwater attractions like Jacuzzi and Lazy River in Long Tien Cave\r\nHave fun playing with the giant artificial mushrooms of the pool and water spouting attractions\r\n12:30 depart for Danang city center\r\n1:00 pm have lunch at a restaurant in the center of Danang (Viet Huong restaurant or Hong Phuc restaurant - buffet for drinks)\r\n2:30 pm end the tour, drop off at downtown Da Nang or meet up location', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQRiNFYB2C96CDghlMy_E2mmgcyLkzPS-GY4g&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcTQfoHuYcR_AKnOFX_e04vA5I0sZsLnCnyVgw&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcRMrXDXgUlav-wCyER11oBoM82rmkOSJvkotg&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQOVS6vOhhzF9IJcuWhm367DU8IvsBKxWgueg&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcToPX7bMpfs42YV6cDcR4V2FJXh3LqEilS0Zw&usqp=CAU', 20, '15.968047', '108.019816'),
(13, 'My Son temple tower area', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQUBVVMEcBm_qRKo7iqTTXwoF29pdHx8IuFKg&usqp=CAU', 'Mỹ Sơn thuộc địa phận xã Duy Phú, huyện Duy Xuyên, tỉnh Quảng Nam, cách thành phố Đà Nẵng khoảng 70 km về hướng tây nam, cách thành phố Hội An khoảng 40km.', 'My Son temple temple complex is located in a valley about 2 km in diameter, surrounded by hills and mountains, in a high mountain circuit about 100m to 400m from East Truong Son to My Son to Tra Kieu capital.\r\n\r\nMy Son is the Hindu holy mecca of the Kingdom of Champa. Each king, after ascending the throne, came to My Son to perform a holy baptism, offer offerings and build temples. My Son is the only point of Cham art that has a continuous development from the 7th to the 13th century. At the beginning of the 7th century, King Sambhuvarman built the temple with very sustainable materials. at to this day. The later kings all remodeled the old temples and built new temples to offer to their gods.\r\nThe main temples in My Son worship a Linga or the image of Siva - the protector of the Champa kings. The god worshiped in My Son is Bhadrésvara, the king who founded the first king of the Amaravati region in the late 4th century combined with the name Siva, becoming the main religious worship of the god - king and royal ancestors .In 1885, My Son relic was discovered by a French scholar named M.C Paris. In the early 20th century, two researchers from French Telecommunications, L.Finot and L.de Lajonquière and architect and archeologist H. Parmentier, came to My Son to study epitaph and ant art. Cham sculpture and sculpture. Until the years 1903-1904, the most basic documents about the stele and My Son architectural art were officially published by L.Finot.\r\n\r\nTemple towers in My Son are divided into clusters, built on the same principle. The structure of each cluster consists of a main temple (Kalan), surrounded by small towers or auxiliary structures. The main temple symbolizes Mount Meru - the center of the universe, the place of the gods and the worship of Siva. The auxiliary temples (secondary shrines) worship the gods of heaven. There are also auxiliary buildings, often with tiled roofs, where pilgrims repair and store offerings. Temples of the Cham people do not have windows, only auxiliary buildings have windows.Cham temples and towers are made of bricks and assembled with decorative pieces of sandstone. They are tightly packed and no research has yet identified a binder. After the tower wall was built, the sculptors began to carve flowers, figures, animals ... onto the tower. The technique of Cham sculpting on bricks rarely appears in other art in the area.\r\n\r\nEach temple tower in My Son has 3 main parts: the base of the tower, the base of the tower and the roof of the tower: The base: according to the Champa conception, the base symbolizes the mundane world, usually built on square or rectangular, with large bricks or slate. Around the base are decorated with motifs of patterns, beasts, prayers standing in small arches ...\r\nThe body of the tower: also according to the Champa conception, the body of the tower symbolizes the spiritual world, where people wash away the dust of the world to be able to contact their ancestors and integrate with the gods.\r\nThe roof of the tower: the roof of the tower symbolizes the gods, usually with three stories getting higher and narrower. Each floor fully simulates the structure of the main door and the fake door like the lower floor and is decorated with idols and mounts of the gods in Hinduism such as: god bird, god goose, cow god, elephant, lion. ... The first and second floors at each corner are often decorated with small towers.According to researchers of the ancient Cham tower, the architecture of Cham tower in My Son converges many styles, continuously from the ancient style of the 7th century to the 8th century, the Hoa Lai style of the 8th century to the present. 9th century, Dong Duong style from the middle of the 9th century, My Son style and transition between My Son and Binh Dinh, Binh Dinh style\r\nFor a long time, people still call the temples in My Son in the rhyme A, A ’, B, C, D ... according to the convention of naming and dividing by Henri Parmentier. He leaned on the walls surr', 'https://www.hoangthanhthanglong.vn/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/myson2.jpg@\r\nhttps://www.hoangthanhthanglong.vn/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/myson3.jpg@\r\nhttps://www.hoangthanhthanglong.vn/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/myson4.jpg@\r\nhttps://www.hoangthanhthanglong.vn/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/myson5.jpg@\r\nhttps://www.hoangthanhthanglong.vn/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/myson6.jpg', 3, '15.764107', '108.124255'),
(14, 'Da Nang Museum', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcSljp_2jD1dQ4b9ZIJ-UzAf49Vn9ZpqfBpBaA&usqp=CAU', 'được xây dựng mới tại địa điểm số 24 Trần Phú (phường Thạch Thang, quận Hải Châu), trong khuôn viên Di tích Quốc gia đặc biệt Thành Điện Hải', 'Da Nang Museum was established in 1989, newly built at 24 Tran Phu (Thach Thang ward, Hai Chau district), within the precinct of Thanh Dien Hai Special National Monument. Danang Museum is invested display facilities, audio-visual equipment and modern lighting systems. The speakers, guides and visitors are well trained. Da Nang Museum was officially inaugurated, opened to visitors on April 26, 2011. The exhibition space with an area of ​​over 3000m2 including 3 floors introduces more than 2,500 documents, images and valuable artifacts. about the history and culture of Da Nang city and its vicinity; including more than 1,900 original artifacts collected from the day of liberation up to now, especially with many precious artifacts, first released to the publicThe opening space of the Da Nang Museum is a solemn space, designed in an arc shape, inspired by the Da Nang earth as a big embrace embracing the sea. At the center of this space is a picture of 5 sails, representing the coastal city reaching out to the big sea, on which depicts the reliefs with the content: Da Nang in the historical process of the country.', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcRlHeXXXEBlp5uBVAyCLF4z0b99QtJL_WyV5A&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcSIhqBn_YrTxCSBErIjDIW7fZAlS_gY1qcekg&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcT5ezcKP3ObGiHnfNf6PDP_0QPmnhviWKmBjw&usqp=CAU', 4, '16.076400', '108.221610'),
(15, 'Làng Vân', 'https://dulichkhampha24.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/lang-van-da-nang-1.jpg', 'Van Village is a small village located right at the foot of Hai Van Pass, also a Da Nang place for young people to enjoy the experience.', 'Van Village is a small village located right at the foot of Hai Van Pass, also a Da Nang place for young people to enjoy the experience. The village is also known as Lep village and Phong village because it used to be the residence of a part of lepers. After integration, people returned to integrate with the community, and from there, the village was abandoned.However, thanks to the beautiful scenery, it is the color of the mountains and the sea, the sand stretches along the charming curve. Mixed in the pristine natural setting are the abandoned houses that have broken. The combination of wild and desolate features makes Van Da Nang village a \"mysterious\" destination that stimulates the curiosity and discovery of many people.\r\n\r\nHow to move to Van village like?\r\nVan village is isolated from the city because there is no straight road leading to it. To travel to Van village, you can choose one of three ways:\r\n\r\n- The first is by boat: This is the simplest way. Everyone went all the way to Nguyen Tat Thanh, met the bend, then turned towards Highway 1A, went to the place where the people in you asked them and then rented a boat to the village.- The second is from down the mountain: This way takes a lot of energy, you need to have health and passion to overcome. Accordingly, you ride a motorbike to Hai Van Pass. From the foot of the pass up about 2-3 km, you will see a small restaurant on the right, you park there (the price is from 20,000 - 30,000 VND / overnight or not). After that, ask for directions and walk for about 1 km to reach the village.\r\n\r\n- The third is walking through the tunnel: According to Da Nang tourism experience to save time, this is the most preferred route. When you reach the foot of the pass, go up the train line 11 and down the tunnel. The road is about 1 km long, quite dark so it is quite difficult to travel. Remember to ask when the train runs and when traveling close to the edge to avoid danger. Cross the tunnel and go another 500 meters to the end.What is particularly attractive to Van Danang Village?\r\nAdmire the natural beauty of Van village\r\nTraveling to Da Nang Van Village is one of the extremely interesting experiences. The first thing to mention is the scenery. Experiencing many ups and downs and fluctuations, Van village is still peaceful on the beach. A peaceful place that is hard to get anywhere, no road dust nor cars, fresh air, gentle scenery between the mountains and the sea. If once \"lost\" here you will enjoy not wanting to leave. It seems that the space clears all sorrow and the bustling city out there, a great place for those who want to find a sense of relaxation.Canoeing on Van Da Nang beach\r\nIn the village beaches visitors can rent canoes to experience. The water here is extremely blue. Usually the boats and canoes will go for 4 to 8 people so you do not bring too much furniture will affect the journey. The canoe gliding quickly on the surface of the water will let you open your eyes to the surrounding of the majestic Hai Van mountain pass, the immense sea, ...\r\n\r\nVan Village Danang - the most ideal camping site\r\nTraveling to Van Da Nang village, young people can choose to camp right next to the beach. But this is also a big challenge for your delegation. This area is divided into 3 distinct lhu, you choose the 3 graves as your camping site.', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcRLDV-MzwX7tFwQrfFOx1q19472yLF3dJPGBA&usqp=CAU@\r\nhttps://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQxHyuN-qTAAgi6MwyvJKd9kw_mxT-skn-NSw&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcSvoLSB3bgwzaOgNgmgInjFwH_I5YIRebDnKA&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQxoAh6rQzBgdskkZ-9jcv21uvyf1LWGyQE_A&usqp=CAU', 5, '16.200007', '108.133336');
