(31, 'Route 2: Kim Lien - Han Market', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcS2nnLyb-WMC38oY4j06s-FcJ9qxqXzNCQ_NQ&usqp=CAU', 'The first leg: Kim Lien - Nguyen Luong Bang - Ton Duc Thang - Dien Bien Phu - Ly Thai To - Hung Vuong - Tran Phu - Tran Quoc Toan - Bach Dang.', 'This is an urban bus route that picks up passengers on a route at nearly 40 stops across the city, mainly concentrated in front of the gates of universities, hospitals, and commercial centers. This route operates from 5h30 to 18h daily with a frequency of 10 minutes / trip during peak hours and 15 minutes / trip during normal hours. In this route, there are 2 cars sponsored by Big C supermarket system. Passengers will be free tickets when there is a voucher for the day at Big C Da Nang supermarket.\r\n\r\nThe first leg: Kim Lien - Nguyen Luong Bang - Ton Duc Thang - Dien Bien Phu - Ly Thai To - Hung Vuong - Tran Phu - Tran Quoc Toan - Bach Dang.\r\n\r\nThe return itinerary: is like the route from Kim Lien to Han Market, which is calculated back to the end.\r\n\r\nTicket price: there are many levels depending on the route of customers, an average of 5,000 VND / time (for the Korean market - bus station) to 10,000 VND / time (for guests traveling throughout the route).', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcS2nnLyb-WMC38oY4j06s-FcJ9qxqXzNCQ_NQ&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcTqRBqWC_i6TAWuG8XPr5T6fdU0cd_y77mWkw&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcTRGfussfKUT9UKSOjkg2tjTK0kcpFPdlk6Cw&usqp=CAU', 26, '16.068262', '108.224268'),
(32, 'Motorbike rental shop in Da Nang - Le Truong', 'https://dulichkhampha24.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/cho-thu-xe-may-da-nang.jpg', 'Address: 92/19 Thi Sach - Da Nang', 'Motorbike rental shop in Da Nang - Le Truong\r\nAddress: 92/19 Thi Sach - Da Nang\r\nLe Truong motorbike rental service is only about 200 meters from the airport, which is very convenient for receiving and returning the car. Once you have your arrival schedule, you just need to call ahead to pick up and drop off your car at the airport. Or to make sure you can also move to the store to choose for yourself the car that you like best. Not only delivery at the airport but also free delivery at other locations such as train stations, hotels and bus stations.Quality of the car ensures, will prepare 1 liter of gasoline, 2 raincoats and 2 helmets. Rents range from VND 100k to VND 150k / day depending on the type of car and the rental period (multi-day rentals will be cheaper). There are all kinds of digital cars and scooters such as wave, sirius, jupiter, airblade, lead, vision…. To book a car, you can contact us directly by phone: 0977.000.744 to meet A. School.', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQnxhM8h0QI146doAwr8c7JUmVCIy6-x-4joA&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQCeLjww-i4QhVq3pgzxCVPLAzXvwTbu-ij4w&usqp=CAU', 27, '16.054405', '108.205515'),
(33, 'Tri Racing Shop', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcSEhgYepVfRWJyk4Hf92K_7HGWIKH8mqQeaBg&usqp=CAU', 'Address: 18 Nguyễn Thị Minh Khai - TP. Danang', 'Receiving a lot of positive feedback from car associations in Da Nang, TRI RACING SHOP with a team of experienced repairmen, always serving and repairing with the most enthusiastic spirit. Customer care system, the best warranty with the motto of customer satisfaction is a measure of Shop success.Especially at the store specializing in the distribution of genuine motorcycle spare parts. Wholesale and retail of spare parts imported from famous brands in the world such as BMC, Barracuda, YSS, Bikers, Ohlins, Denso, Bando, Zhi.Pat, Michelin, Dunlop, Metzeler, Liqui Moly, Mobil 1 Gold, etc.Contact information Tri Racing Shop - Service center for repair and repair of scooters in Da Nang\r\nAddress: 18 Nguyễn Thị Minh Khai - TP. Danang\r\nPhone: 0935.969.789\r\nWebsite: www.t-racing.vn\r\nFanPage: www.facebook.com/triracingshop/\r\nOpening time: from 8am to 6pm. Even Sunday. Holidays.', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcRc_ZttpKy3eyF6dCFPOu26KI5nxQjAP7awiw&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcTnfL-DwB3EtLrABJrEaMK8a7rqEXqyyTPmLg&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcSEhgYepVfRWJyk4Hf92K_7HGWIKH8mqQeaBg&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcRvx8iwOliYyqIwCoDDvg7MIjyrE_sE1uak2w&usqp=CAU', 28, '16.075537', '108.217744'),
(34, 'Petrol Station No. 2', 'https://diadiem.danang.gov.vn/Portals/0/Photo/101/101.jpg', '627 Nguyen Luong Bang, Hoa Hiep Nam, Lien Chieu', 'Copyright of Danang People\'s Committee\r\nLicense: 612 / GP-STTTT issued on October 21, 2016\r\nChief Editor: Le Trung Chinh, Vice Chairman of City People\'s Committee\r\nHeadquarters: The web portal of Da Nang city\r\nAddress: 24 Trần Phú, Q. Hải Châu, TP. Danang. Email: toasoan@danang.gov.vn\r\nPhone: (84 236) 3826338, Fax (84 236) 3821286', 'https://diadiem.danang.gov.vn/Portals/0/Photo/101/101.jpg@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcTLbc8X98C1X8ITnIXBTvaMgmo4rtzaJRz19Q&usqp=CAU', 29, '16.094825', '108.138291'),
(35, 'Danang International Airport', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQsTCZcpKilXeFixnK2ugmykxs1ZCgBe9cXcA&usqp=CAU', 'Da Nang International Airport is the largest airport in the Central region and the Central Highlands and the third largest in Vietnam, located in Hai Chau district, 3 km from the center of Danang city', 'Da Nang International Airport is the largest airport in the Central region and the Central Highlands and the third largest in Vietnam, located in Hai Chau district, 3 km from the center of Danang city, with a total area of ​​the yard area. Flight 842 ha, of which the area of ​​civil aviation is 150 ha. This is an important flight point for Central Vietnam and the whole country.\r\n\r\nThe official transaction name is Da Nang International Airport (English: Danang International Airport - DIA). The airport was formerly operated by the Central Airport Corporation, now under the Vietnam Airport Corporation, an enterprise under the Ministry of Transport.\r\n\r\nThe number of passengers in 2019 at the airport is 15.5 million, which is the third-largest airport in Vietnam.History\r\nThe airport was built in 1940. During the Vietnam War until 1975, Da Nang airport was the air base of the US Army and the Republic of Vietnam Air Force. Before 1975, Danang International Airport was one of the busiest airports in the world.\r\n\r\nWork\r\nCurrently, there are 5 domestic airlines and 38 international airlines having routes to Danang International Airport, the 3rd most in the country. From Da Nang, there are 16 domestic routes, 51 international routes including 25 regular direct flights and 26 direct charter routes, with more than 250 domestic and international flights every day, helping convenient connection with major transfer stations of Asia and the world such as Incheon-Korea, Narita-Japan, Changi-Singapore, Doha-Qatar, Dai Hung-China, New Delhi-India ...\r\n\r\n\r\nCustoms Department of Danang Airport\r\nIn 2015, Da Nang International Airport was ranked 23rd in the Top 30 Best Airports in Asia, according to information published on the website of the world\'s major airport rankings The Guide to Sleeping in Airports . In 2019, Da Nang international airport was organized to evaluate and rank the global airport and airport - SKYTRAX ranked 3-star standard +, T2 international terminal achieved 4-star standard.', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQPP-XWsqJvg3ZuZmzKYXCQPkiB3z4YojjVLw&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcTcVROZQn7ouFRUdSHIrqPikZz6z4zCjvWjcw&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcSv6O8IBpzsCiMEBAyWCykAMfD13faRWR8OVQ&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQsTCZcpKilXeFixnK2ugmykxs1ZCgBe9cXcA&usqp=CAU', 30, '16.056305', '108.200829'),
(36, 'Danang Railway Station', 'https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c0/Da_Nang_Train_Stn_Front.JPG/300px-Da_Nang_Train_Stn_Front.JPG', 'located at Hoa Minh ward, Lien Chieu district', 'Da Nang Railway Station was built and inaugurated in 1902 according to the unified architecture from South to North. Since its foundation, Da Nang railway station has been repaired and built many times so there are no traces of the old architecture. After the liberation of the South, Da Nang station was expanded to become a section station with three functions: cargo, passenger and technical operations, which is now one of the most important stations on the route. North - South iron. The North-South railway route running through Danang has a length of about 30 km. Every day there are many trains from Hanoi Railway Station and Saigon Railway Station to Danang. All current transatlantic trains stop picking up and dropping off passengers at the station. From Da Nang station, passengers can buy tickets to all stations in the country.\r\n\r\nAt present, Da Nang station is one of the largest and best in Central Vietnam (standard of grade 1 station and Vinh station). Newly upgraded station is spacious and clean; there is a boat lounge equipped with air conditioning, fully equipped, accommodating about 200 people and many additional services to serve passengers such as restaurants, bars, public phones, newsstands, bathing area, toilet ..., security and order in the station area is guaranteed.Currently, the city and the Ministry of Transport are promoting a project to relocate the station out of the city center for 6 years from 2017 to 2023. The new passenger terminal is 43.1 ha, located in Hoa Minh ward, Lien Chieu district. The cargo terminal is Kim Lien Station with an area of ​​80 hectares, located in Hoa Hiep Bac Ward in Lien Chieu District and upgrading Le Trach Station with an area of ​​9.6 hectares.', 'https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c0/Da_Nang_Train_Stn_Front.JPG/300px-Da_Nang_Train_Stn_Front.JPG@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcTaWWuuXa55bpiuMquio-Vekk4Sb8xRWBWDjg&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcSY1_csuWsjvP3x1Y8UKT8b6V5UXVZRGAZRJg&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcSqyWLXbtKwGonyTbW5ten4DsYJ6ayJ8XF2Tg&usqp=CAU', 31, '16.071710', '108.209309'),
(37, 'First 6-storey car park in Danang', 'https://vcdn1-vnexpress.vnecdn.net/2019/10/14/a9-1571028746.jpg?w=1200&h=0&q=100&dpr=1&fit=crop&s=7Xn2Qel6sfIhbbGNTLQMVA', 'Thach Thang, Hai Chau, Da Nang 550000, Vietnam', 'The first smart car park in Danang was built at 255 Phan Chau Trinh (Hai Chau district), with an area of ​​1,000 m2. The first stage consists of 6 floors (5 compartments each floor) designed in steel form. Phase 2 is being called for investment by the city, with the assembly area being the vacant land opposite to phase 1.The yard has a capacity of 50 parking positions of 4-7 seats, with a total investment of nearly 28 billion VND from the budget, invested by the Department of Transport and Transport.\r\n\r\nParking will be put into use to help reduce traffic congestion in the central area, especially Nguyen Van Linh route due to too many cars parked on the road.In September, the car park is put into trial operation. In October, the car will be opened and sent by people. At the gate is an automatic guarding system.\r\n\r\nThe site of this parking lot was formerly a public house. In 2018, Da Nang has recalled and planned to make smart parking.', 'https://vcdn1-vnexpress.vnecdn.net/2019/10/14/a9-1571028746.jpg?w=1200&h=0&q=100&dpr=1&fit=crop&s=7Xn2Qel6sfIhbbGNTLQMVA@https://vcdn1-vnexpress.vnecdn.net/2019/10/11/A3-1570809801.jpg?w=1200&h=0&q=100&dpr=1&fit=crop&s=Qfrayx_vVrw86RMoe88aLg@https://vcdn1-vnexpress.vnecdn.net/2019/10/14/a4-1571028612.jpg?w=1200&h=0&q=100&dpr=1&fit=crop&s=RAXa5VWEMjAeCUJEVeT5Eg@https://vcdn1-vnexpress.vnecdn.net/2019/10/14/a3-1571028964.jpg?w=1200&h=0&q=100&dpr=1&fit=crop&s=Jmf1YyjvItjqoB_8hbQkdg', 32, '16.076291', '108.223112'),
(38, 'The School of Medicine and Pharmacy - The University of Danang (SMP)', 'https://tuyensinhso.vn/images/files/tuyensinhso.com/khoa-y-duoc-dh-da-nang.jpg', 'Address: Urban University of Danang, P. Hoa Quy, Q. Ngu Hanh Son, TP. Danang', 'School name: Faculty of Medicine - Da Nang University\r\nEnglish name: The School of Medicine and Pharmacy - The University of Danang (SMP)\r\nSchool code: DDY\r\nType of school: Public\r\nTraining system: University\r\nAddress: Urban University of Danang, P. Hoa Quy, Q. Ngu Hanh Son, TP. Danang\r\nTelephone: (84.236) .3990458 - 0236.399.0461\r\nEmail: smp@ac.udn.vn - daotao@smp.udn.vn\r\nWebsite: http://smp.udn.vn/\r\nFacebook: www.facebook.com/smp.dhdn/', 'https://tuyensinhso.vn/images/files/tuyensinhso.com/khoa-y-duoc-dh-da-nang.jpg@https://tuyensinhso.vn/images/files/tuyensinhso.com/khoa-y-duoc-dh-da-nang-1.JPG@', 34, '15.984969', '108.229150'),
(39, 'Phan Chau Trinh High School', 'https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPVewNFutG-N_LmjTV8P6kmkKQ1X3EU-vAGyfgF=w408-h306-k-no', '154 Le Loi, Thach Thang, Hai Chau, Da Nang 550000, Vietnam', 'Phan Chau Trinh High School is a public high school formally established on September 15, 1952, in Hai Chau, Da Nang. The school is one of the prestigious education units, training high quality human resources in the city. [1]September 15, 1952, the school was established, located at the current Phu Dong Primary School.\r\nIn the school year 1954 - 1955, the school was built at 167 Le Loi (the former school of the current school) and officially named Phan Chau Trinh High School.\r\nIn the school year 1975 - 1976, the school\'s organizational system changed, the school became Phan Chau Trinh High School, then became Phan Chau Trinh High School as it is now.\r\nFrom the 2004-2005 school year, the school built a new campus at 154 Le Loi.\r\nOn April 15, 2015, Da Nang City approved the commencement of rebuilding the old Phan Chau Trinh High School (No. 167 Le Loi) on an area of ​​6,807m² [2]\r\n• Scale of training: In the school year of 1952 - 1953, the school had a grade of Seventh grade (grade 6); By the school year of 1974 - 1975, the school had 68 classes of Junior High and High School. In the school year 2002 - 2003, the school had 74 classes with nearly 4,000 students. School year 2012 - 2013, the school has 98 classes with more than 4,700 students. And in the 2013-2014 school year, the school had 97 classes - 4,400 students.\r\n\r\nAchievements', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQ1Zt3jd_STx9kzPlS2rpmJlvnLwMCh2dcgKQ&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcTPKQ3jOiRxp_HOutnpOhUGnf3I1HlXcLC1Vw&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQffFnlpmx47WlsDyA8v530PRXwkEJIJ2jGLg&usqp=CAU', 33, '16.071975', '108.219723'),
(40, 'Danang Library', 'http://thuvienquocgia.vn/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/thu-vien-da-nang-noi-yen-tinh-va-dep-nhu-phim-han.jpg', 'Located on Bach Dang street is the most beautiful street in Da Nang city. The Danang Library is both a symbol of the city\'s architectural symbol and a destination for the community.', 'Where is the Danang Library? Located on Bach Dang street is the most beautiful street in Da Nang city. The Danang Library is both a symbol of the city\'s architectural symbol and a destination for the community.\r\n\r\nAccording to the news, after the renovation and upgrading time, the Danang General Science Library (Da Nang Library) has been completed and is a great place for readers. Da Nang Library is one of 11 key projects of Danang city2. The book icon opens at Da Nang library\r\nThe Da Nang Library or the Danang General Science Library is renovated. Upgrade to a new library like an open book. The icon of the book opened at the library of Da Nang city was inaugurated and put into use on August 31, 2015. Has attracted the attention of readers of all ages, all professions.\r\n\r\nWhere is the Danang Library? Perhaps this is a question many people need to be answered. With an area of ​​construction is not small, 2,000m2 in the area of ​​7,270m2 wide, with 2 gates. The main gate of Da Nang library is facing Bach Dang street. The back gate faces Tran Phu street. The project has a total investment of VND 50, 8 billion. Library blocks, administrative areas and many other items have been invested in new modern equipment.', 'https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcTxm-VyBor0IZMebRBaEuJGCjo-DKMHT2ETJw&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcTa94pUZLYldtiv4FSFe3frB-d9RNSUTgM1wg&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcRuyRB3jSnoc5EAgsIO4hZ3uE0QD-UtxpxITA&usqp=CAU@https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQGItjHyFdmn3tHXCvXTtSnRHaGfeYJOIFSSA&usqp=CAU', 35, '16.073725', '108.224085')